  "prompt": "A bag contains 5 white, 7 red and 8 black balls. If four balls are drawn one by one without replacement, what is the probability of getting all white balls?",
  "response": "Let $W$ be the number of white balls in the bag, $R$ be the number of red balls in the bag, and $B$ be the number of black balls in the bag.\nWe are given that $W=5$, $R=7$, $B=8$. The total number of balls in the bag is $N = W+R+B = 5+7+8 = 20$.\nWe want to find the probability of drawing four white balls one by one without replacement.\n\nLet $A_i$ be the event that the $i$-th ball drawn is white, for $i=1,2,3,4$.\nWe want to find the probability $P(A_1 \\cap A_2 \\cap A_3 \\cap A_4)$.\nSince the balls are drawn without replacement, the events are dependent.\nWe can write\n$P(A_1 \\cap A_2 \\cap A_3 \\cap A_4) = P(A_1) P(A_2|A_1) P(A_3|A_1 \\cap A_2) P(A_4|A_1 \\cap A_2 \\cap A_3)$\nThe probability that the first ball drawn is white is $P(A_1) = \\frac{5}{20}$.\nIf the first ball drawn is white, there are now 4 white balls and 19 total balls left.\nSo $P(A_2|A_1) = \\frac{4}{19}$.\nIf the first two balls drawn are white, there are now 3 white balls and 18 total balls left.\nSo $P(A_3|A_1 \\cap A_2) = \\frac{3}{18}$.\nIf the first three balls drawn are white, there are now 2 white balls and 17 total balls left.\nSo $P(A_4|A_1 \\cap A_2 \\cap A_3) = \\frac{2}{17}$.\nTherefore,\n$$P(A_1 \\cap A_2 \\cap A_3 \\cap A_4) = \\frac{5}{20} \\cdot \\frac{4}{19} \\cdot \\frac{3}{18} \\cdot \\frac{2}{17} = \\frac{5 \\cdot 4 \\cdot 3 \\cdot 2}{20 \\cdot 19 \\cdot 18 \\cdot 17} = \\frac{120}{116280} = \\frac{1}{969}$$\n\nWe can also think of this as choosing 4 balls out of 20.\nThe number of ways to choose 4 balls out of 20 is $\\binom{20}{4} = \\frac{20!}{4!16!} = \\frac{20 \\cdot 19 \\cdot 18 \\cdot 17}{4 \\cdot 3 \\cdot 2 \\cdot 1} = 5 \\cdot 19 \\cdot 3 \\cdot 17 = 4845$.\nThe number of ways to choose 4 white balls out of 5 is $\\binom{5}{4} = \\frac{5!}{4!1!} = 5$.\nSo the probability of choosing 4 white balls is\n$\\frac{\\binom{5}{4}}{\\binom{20}{4}} = \\frac{5}{4845} = \\frac{1}{969}$.\n\nFinal Answer: The final answer is $\\boxed{1/969}$",
